Table tag
-> <table> defines a table

Attributes of table tag
-> border: it specifies the width of the border around a table
-> cellpadding: it specifies the space between the cell wall and cell content
-> cellspacing: it specifies the space between cells
-> align: value can be left, center or right)
-> width: specifies the width of a table
-> bgcolor: specifies a background color of a table
     -color name("pink")
     -Hex code of color name ("#ffA000")
     -rgb number("rgb(255,0,0)")

<tr> tag define row in a table
<th> tag define a table header ( text is bold and center aligned)
<td> tag defines table data    ( text is not bold and is left aligned)

Attributes for <th> and <td>
-> align: left,right,center,justify
-> bgcolor: color name, rgb(), hexcode
-> colspan = number (if you want one column in a row instead of two then you can use colspan="2")
-> rowspan = number
-> height = pixel or percentage
-> valign = top,middle,bottom.
-> width = pixel or percentage

Example
<html>
<head>
<title> Welcome to table tag pagee </title>
</head>
<body>
<table border="2px">
<tr>
<th> S.No. </th>
<th> Subjects </th>
<th> Grade </th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td> 1 </td>
<td>  Physics </td>
<td> A </td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td> 2 </td>
<td> C++ </td>
<td> B+ </td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td colspan="2"> Total SGPA </td>
<td> 8.0 </td>
</tr>

</table>
</body>
</html>
